{
    "name": "Boggard Scouting Party",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Boggard Scouting Party",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Boggard scouting parties run ahead of other boggard troops to get the lay of the land. They sometimes engage if they think they can quickly vanquish an enemy force.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Battlecry!",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Battlecry! pg. 175",
                        "alt": "Battlecry! pg. 175",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 268
                    },
                    "page": 175
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Boggard",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Boggard Villages",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Boggards prefer to dwell in swamplands and mires. Though they are at home in the water, they prefer to spend most of their lives on land and build villages of mud huts. They often keep guardian beasts, such as crocodiles, giant frogs, or other feral animals tamed (if only just barely) to serve as protectors.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Monster Core",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Monster Core pg. 44",
