                                "name": "grabbed",
                                "alt": "grabbed",
                                "game-obj": "Conditions",
                                "aonid": 77
                            }
                        ],
                        "frequency": "once per round",
                        "effect": "Several boggards use their tongues to grapple an enemy within 10 feet to pull them closer. The target must attempt a DC 21 Reflex save. On a failure, they are grabbed and pulled 5 feet closer to the scouting party. A creature grabbed in this way isn't immobilized, but it can't move more than 10 feet from the scouting party. A creature can sever one of the tongues with a Strike against AC 21 that deals at least 5 slashing damage. This doesn't damage the scouting party."
                    }
                },
